State whether the following statements are true or false. Give reasons for your answers. (i) Every natural number is a whole number.

The statement is true since the collection of whole numbers contains all natural numbers. (ii) Every integer is a whole number.

No, the statement is false, as integers may be negative but whole numbers are always positive.

(iii) Every rational number is a whole number.

No, the statement is false, as rational numbers may be fractional but whole numbers may not be.
